  "description": "Forming part of Islington Council's Capital Works Programme, the proposed communal works will be taking place to 59-93 Liverpool Road:\r\n\r\n•\tInternal flat entrance door replacements with fire door sets and architraves which are non-original (abbreviated as FD30S.)\r\n•\tFanlights above doors, when applicable.\r\n•\tInstallation of new fire alarm systems\r\n•\tElectrical cupboard replacement, when applicable like for like. \r\n•\tEmergency lighting within common areas only. \r\n\r\nForming part of Islington Council's Capital Works Programme, the proposed basement works will be taking place:\r\n\r\n•\tRemove boilers and ducting from the boiler room\r\n•\tRemove asbestos from the boiler room\r\n•\tRemove any redundant cabling and pipework from the basement\r\n•\tInstall a 120-minute fire rated ceiling with 60-minute access panels where required\r\n•\tInstall 60-minute fire doors between each property’s basement\r\n•\tFire stops between each area\r\n•\tRun a sub-main and install a landlords fuseboard in the boiler room\r\n•\tInstall lighting to all basement areas\r\n•\tInstall a fire detection system to all basement areas",
